finally after almost a year, I have the gut to start rolling again! 😅 cukup senang dgn hasil nya, ada improvement/progress! skrg bentuknya beneran sudah menyerupai croissant hahaha. yaah meskipun ini underproof ya, atau roll nya masih jelek 😅 ntah lah kalo udah dikejar waktu jd panik jd ga bs mikir step nya 😐 croissant ini technical ya, hrs dipikir mau roll pas jam brp dll krn kita di negara tropis. setiap 1/2 jam hrs dikembalikan ke kulkas, atau in between the roll misal butter mulai leleh, cepat2 masuk kulkas lg & tanpa mesin! sensasi saat buat croissant ini rasanya kita seperti pengen d dalam kulkas terus 🤣 semoga berikut2nya bisa lebih bagus lg yes? #croissantwarrior #homemadecroissant #selflaminate #fullbuttercroissant

Tried milk bread recipe by @icenguik and modified using kinako powder and taro powder. It’s roasted soybean flour and most commonly used to coat mochi. But many also use this to make bread even softer. 
My first experience with kinako is that it absorbs more liquid 😊 There is always something new to learn💃🏻

udah kangen ngeroti pdhal baru saja buat roti ini bbrp hari yg lalu 😅 resep roti manis @jensoee ini enaakkk.. pertama kali membuat roti yg resepnya menggunakan susu evaporasi, aku pake merk Sunbay. memang proses resepnya ada tambahan steps, tp hasil tentu tidak mengkhianati proses 😊 resep ini akan jd salah satu resep andalan utk roti manis basic 👍🏻 bentuknya menyerupai sisir? hahaha ga mirip? mirip2in lah udaaa.. 🙄😝

Thank you for 1000 followers! hope it doesn’t go to 999 by the time I posted this 😅 so thankful for this platform, where I can share my hobby, both the successes and the failures, even in the limited time that we have. also found friends with the same hobby and being our true self.
Like this 🍞 cube of bread, I once read that life wouldn’t be fun if all the sides are perfectly coming together as you wish..well, same like baking, too. We showed our progress off to other baking friends, knowing that it’s the hard work and resilience which got us here. So I am thankful, for all the faith & fun that baking has brought us together. Let’s learn by process, and not by result.
(last pic: my imperfect 🍞)
